main event: An observer reported seeing numerous white or silver fuzzy elongated lights appearing to be planes and disappearing over the bay in Annapolis, Maryland, on January 2, 1968.
interesting points: The observer saw the lights moving rapidly in succession and believed they were too frequent for conventional aircraft,The phenomena was reported to have lasted for 11 hours and involved multiple sightings,The lights were theorized to possibly be reflections of searchlights on clouds due to weather conditions at the time,The Annapolis Police Department received no unusual reports despite the observer's claims of many sightings,The observer initially suspected the lights were rockets being discharged from a nearby site.
sighted object: white or silver fuzzy elongated lights
witness description: The witness was a resident who reported the sighting after returning home with family.
